rComments: Great Prof, extremely personable and super nice. Always approachable about questions and just to chat with. Tough marker but understands personal circumstances.

I dont understand why everyones hating on Timbers, I had her for my 1st year history at Trent and she was huge at getting me acquainted to university quality research. Helpful when I was in a jam also. Dont be intimidated, while she can seem a little scary sometimes shes actually pretty cool

"Guest" prof at Trent University.  Knows her subject, but does not know how to convey it to students.  Unrealistic marker and offers no constructive criticism to explain the low marks.  Requires students to purchase out-of-print books beyond the required text in syllabus.  Time-consuming and expensive.  Condescending in seminar.  AVOID!
Boring, went about the subject matter in an inefficient way. Too much attention to paintings and anecdotes (not very helpful ones either) and not enough to facts.
She needs to lay of the WIKIPEDIA for a change, why you ask?.. because she can't lecture..

WHAT an amazing professor. Timbers is one of the clearest speakers I know. She inspired me to pursue more history courses in Early Modern Europe. She has a great sense of humour and she can teach very well, even to a novice like me. I would recommend any class by her.

She is an exceptional prof! Her lectures are very comprehensive as well as interesting. She is also very helpful and always wanting to involve the class, so as to not make students feel bored. I'm just disappointed that I had to take this course in the summer and wasn't able to during normal school term! ps saved money not having required textbook.
